text: Tijana Bogdanović (, born 5 May 1998) is a Serbian taekwondo practitioner. ==Career== Bogdanović won a gold medal at the 2016 European Taekwondo Championships, but failed to defend the title two years later in Kazan, claiming there bronze. During the 2016 Summer Olympics, she competed in the Women's 49 kg category, winning a silver medal. She has qualified to represent Serbia at the 2020 Summer Olympics in the women's 49 kg category. ==Personal life== Bogdanović lives in Belgrade, Serbia. ==References== Category:Serbian female taekwondo practitioners Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Kruševac Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Serbia Category:European Games silver medalists for Serbia Category:European Games medalists in taekwondo Category:Olympic taekwondo practitioners of Serbia Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic silver medalists for Serbia Category:Olympic medalists in taekwondo Category:European champions for Serbia Category:Universiade medalists in taekwondo Category:Universiade gold medalists for Serbia Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:European Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Medalists at the 2017 Summer Universiade
